data-triple-N3.o: "The Han Dynasty (206 BC 220 AD) was an imperial dynasty of China, preceded by the Qin Dynasty (221207 BC) and succeeded by the Three Kingdoms (220280 AD). It was founded by the rebel leader Liu Bang, known posthumously as Emperor Gaozu of Han. It was briefly interrupted by the Xin Dynasty (923 AD) of the former regent Wang Mang. This interregnum separates the Han into two periods: the Western Han (206 BC 9 AD) and Eastern Han (25220 AD)."@en
